    "sitg_founder": {
      "type": "sitg-founder",
      "settings": {
        "eyebrow": "Why I built this",
        "headline": "I LIVED OUT OF CARRY-ONS<br>FOR 11 YEARS.",
        "story": "<p>I spent 11 years as a flight attendant. Two thousand flights. Forty-seven countries. I lived out of carry-ons before any influencer made it a lifestyle.</p><p>And in all that time, I never owned a single bag I actually loved. The premium designer cases were beautiful but useless — no garment bay, no shoe compartment, scuffed in a month. The functional travel bags were ugly. <strong>Every bag I tried made me choose: beautiful, or practical. Never both.</strong></p><p>So I built one. I started by drafting the bag I would have wanted on my first 5am London-Milan turnaround. Then I tested 41 prototypes against the actual chaos of cabin life — gate sizers, overhead lockers, the back of a Heathrow taxi at 11pm.</p><p><strong>HerVoyage is what I would have killed to own at 26.</strong> It's the bag I never had — the one that makes you look effortless when you're anything but.</p><p>Now ten thousand women have it. They send me photos from Tokyo, from São Paulo, from a hotel breakfast in Marrakech, hair perfect, dress wrinkle-free. They write things like: <em>\"I will never check a bag again.\"</em></p><p>Neither will I.</p>",
        "pullquote": "I wasn't waiting for someone else to design it. So I built it myself.",
        "pullquote_attribution": "— Founder, HerVoyage",
        "signature": "— Still travelling. Still beautiful. Still HerVoyage."
      }
    },
